\int\frac{dx}{1+x^2}=\tan^{-1}x+C
x=\tan\theta,dx=\sec^2\theta d\theta
\int\frac{dx}{1+x^2}=\int\frac{\sec^2\theta d\theta}{1+\tan^2\theta}=\int\frac{\sec^2\theta d\theta}{\sec^2\theta}=\int d\theta=\theta+C
